DIGEST
SB 352 Original 2026 Regular Session Carter
Present law provides for registered owners of vehicles or trailers of vehicles to make prompt
payment to the department if the proper toll is not paid and an administrative fee of $25.
Proposed law changes the administrative fee from $25 to no more than two percent of the
total cost of the toll, not including a late charge of five dollars.
Present law provides the registered owner is prima facie responsible for the payment of the
toll, administrative fees, and late charges assessed by the department. Proposed law deletes
present law.
Effective August 1, 2026.
(Amends R.S. 48:250.4.1(C) and (D))
